f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Help Scout is best suited for small businesses, SaaS startups, customer focused teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Ultimate.ai, meanwhile, shines for enterprise support, multilingual teams, CX automation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2011, Help Scout describes itself as \"Simple and human customer support platform with AI-powered features.\" Ultimate.ai, established in 2016, positions itself as \"AI-powered virtual agent platform for automating customer service interactions.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Help Scout** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 8). However, this does not mean Ultimate.ai is a poor choice — far from it. Ultimate.ai excels in its own right, particularly for enterprise support and multilingual teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value clean and simple shared inbox, go with Help Scout. If strong multilingual support matters more to you, Ultimate.ai is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
